  "title": "Tail Supremum Sequence",
  "root": "",
  "statement": "Let $(x_n)$ be a bounded real sequence. The \\textbf{tail supremum\nsequence} of $(x_n)$ is the real sequence $(s_n)$ defined by\n\\[\n s_n:=\\sup\\{x_k:k\\ge n\\}\n \\qquad\\text{for every } n\\in\\mathbb{N}.\n\\]",
